In heavy saucepan, combine milk, rice, raisins, syrup, tapioca, egg, lemon peel, and cinnamon. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is very hot and slightly thickened, 7 to 8 minutes. Do not boil. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Cover and let stand until thickened, 20 to 25 minutes. Stir before serving. Serve warm or chilled.